Initially, a parallel bucketsort splits the list into enough sublists then to be sorted in parallel using merge-sort. The parallel bucketsort, implemented in NVIDIAâ€™s CUDA, utilizes the synchronization mechanisms, such as atomic increment, that is available on modern GPUs. 
